## Multimodal content parts

GenAI requests increasingly carry non-text content — images, audio clips, video,
and documents — alongside text. To represent these on spans without inlining
binary data, this convention defines a per-part attribute family with offload
support.

> **Status:** development. The attributes below are additive; emitters that
> don't recognize them MUST NOT fail. Existing text-only traces produce
> byte-identical attributes to releases prior to this addition.

For a request with `N` messages, each carrying `M` content parts, an emitter
SHOULD set:

| Attribute | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.role`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-role) | string | Role of the n-th message author. |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.type`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-type) | enum | One of `text`, `image`, `audio`, `video`, `document`. |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.text`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-text) | string | Text payload (only when `type=text`). |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.media_uri`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-media_uri) | string | URI from which the bytes can be retrieved. |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.media_mime_type`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-media_mime_type) | string | IANA MIME type of the part. |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.media_byte_size`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-media_byte_size) | int | Size in bytes at capture time. |
| [`gen_ai.prompt.{n}.content.{m}.media_source`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-prompt-content-media_source) | enum | `inline_offloaded`, `external_url`, or `reference_only`. |
| [`gen_ai.media.stripped_reason`](/docs/attributes-registry/gen-ai.md#gen_ai-media-stripped_reason) | enum | Set on the span when at least one part's bytes were intentionally not captured. |

The `gen_ai.completion.*` namespace mirrors the same attributes for generated
content (e.g. an image generation result, a TTS audio response).

### `media_source` semantics

- `inline_offloaded` — The caller sent bytes inline (e.g. as a base64
  payload). The instrumentor uploaded them to a configured object store and
  `media_uri` resolves to that copy.
- `external_url` — The caller already provided a URL the model fetched
  directly. The instrumentor did not re-host it. `media_uri` is the original
  URL exactly as supplied by the caller.
- `reference_only` — Bytes were detected but intentionally not stored (for
  compliance or cost reasons). Only the modality, MIME type, and byte size are
  recorded.

### Relationship to `gen_ai.input.messages`

The structured opt-in `gen_ai.input.messages` blob and the flat per-part
attributes are not redundant. The flat attributes are queryable in any OTel
backend without JSON parsing (suitable for dashboards and alerting), while the
JSON blob preserves arbitrary nesting and provider-specific fields the flat
attributes don't model. Emitters MAY emit either or both, controlled by
`OTEL_SEMCONV_STABILITY_OPT_IN` (existing dual-emission pattern).

### Bytes never appear inline

Binary content MUST NOT be encoded into span attribute values. Emitters that
want to capture bytes MUST upload to a store the deployment owns and reference
the result by URI in `media_uri`. This keeps span size predictable and avoids
exfiltrating sensitive content into telemetry pipelines that are not configured
to handle it.
